data.chText: （通常指农村的）大片私有土地，庄园
data.enText: a large area of land, usually in the country, that is owned by one person or family
an area of land with a lot of houses or factories of the same type on it

data.chText: 她住在伦敦某住宅区的一栋高楼里。
data.enText: She lives in a tower block on an estate in London.
all the money and property that a person owns, especially everything that is left when they die
Her estate was left to her daughter.

simple_means.memory_skill: e 加强 + stat 站，立 + e → 立住不动〔但有价值的东西〕→〔房子等〕不动产

means: (通常指农村的)大片私有土地，庄园

tr: a major social class or order of persons regarded collectively as part of the body politic of the country (especially in the United Kingdom) and formerly possessing distinct political rights
extensive landed property (especially in the country) retained by the owner for his own use
example: the family owned a large estate on Long Island

tr: all of your assets (whether real property or personal property) and liabilities

value.def: An estate is a large area of land in the country which is owned by a person, family, or organization.

example.ex: ...a shooting party on Lord Wyville's estate in Yorkshire.
example.tran: 在怀维尔勋爵位于约克郡的庄园里举行的狩猎会

value.tran: 庄园;地产；（在乡村的）大片私有土地

value.def: People sometimes use estate to refer to a housing estate or an industrial estate.

example.ex: He used to live on the estate.
example.tran: 他过去曾住在那个住宅区。

value.def: Someone's estate is all the money and property that they leave behind them when they die.

example.tran: 他的遗产被估价为15万美元。

value.def: An estate is the same as an estate car .

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 station wagon
